reviewText: Just to let you know that this is simply re-packaging of a 2003 film; "Barely Legal Lesbian Vampires: The Curse of Ed Wood" that Amazon sold previously, and also sells as part of a larger collection "Tomb of Terrors 50 Movie Pack". It was bad several years ago. Simply re-badging it doesn't make it better.

reviewText: What can be said about a movie whose stars, and director, are listed as "n/a" in the Amazon description?  Obviously, these people wanted to make some quick cash.....NOT wreck their future careers. Who can blame them?????The title here says it all.  "LESBIAN VAMPIRES".  Vampires, (with exceptions like "Angel" from "Buffy the Vampire" and "Angel", and "Barnabas Collins" from "Dark Shadows"), are usually supposed to be BAD.Lesbians........well, before "political correctness" came about, they too were considered to all be BAD.Put "Lesbian(s)" and "Vampires" together....and you get, (surprise!) a BAD movie!This movie is full of blood, gore, and lust. (Not that I have seen it...I've read other people's reviews).  It has only one redeeming value, in that, (by and large), it must usually keep it's viewers inside either their homes or their friends homes....and OFF THE STREETS!  This movie obviously makes even the "South Park" TV series look good.  I have a very strong suspicion that it insults both REAL lesbians, and, (I_F they exist), real vampires as well.My suggestions?  Watch "Angel".  Watch "Buffy The Vampire Slayer".  Watch "Dark Shadows".  Read: "The Well of Loneliness".And get some energy for the day ahead by going to bed early and getting a good night's sleep!

reviewText: Lesbian Vampires fails in every category it possibly could. It's attempts at humor are not at all funny. To call them sophomoric would be an undeserved complement. It is neither sexy nor scary, which is what would be threshold issues for this kind of movie. The actors are unattractive and there is absolutely no dramatic tension. There is also nothing to admire in the technical qualities of the film. Even the most amateurish camera work and production you've ever seen is superior to this very poor effort. LV has nothing to recommend it.
